                      00001 ;===============================================================================
                      00002 ; PIC16F877A Matrix Keypad & 5x7 LED Display with UART Communication
                      00003 ; Project: ESP8266 MQTT Interface System
                      00004 ;===============================================================================
                      00005 ; Description:
                      00006 ;   - Reads input from 4x8 matrix keypad using interrupt-on-change
                      00007 ;   - Displays pressed character on 5x7 LED matrix (multiplexed)
                      00008 ;   - Transmits ASCII code via UART to ESP8266 at 9600 baud
                      00009 ;   - Supports SHIFT key for uppercase letters
                      00010 ;
                      00011 ; Hardware Configuration:
                      00012 ;   - Clock: 4 MHz
                      00013 ;   - Keypad Rows (Input): RB4-RB7 (with internal pull-ups)
                      00014 ;       Row 0 (Q row) = RB7, Row 3 (SHIFT row) = RB4 (inverted!)
                      00015 ;   - Keypad Columns (Output): RD0-RD7
                      00016 ;       Col 0 = RD7 (MSB), Col 7 = RD0 (LSB)
                      00017 ;   - Display Columns: RA0-RA4 (RA4 is open-drain - needs external pull-up)
                      00018 ;   - Display Rows: RC0-RC5, RA5
                      00019 ;   - UART TX: RC6 (9600 baud)
                      00020 ;===============================================================================
                      00021 
                      00022     LIST P=16F877A
                      00023     #INCLUDE <P16F877A.INC>
                      00001         LIST
                      00002 
                      00003 ;==========================================================================
                      00004 ;  MPASM PIC16F877A processor include
                      00005 ; 
                      00006 ;  (c) Copyright 1999-2013 Microchip Technology, All rights reserved
                      00007 ;==========================================================================
                      00008 
